This paper is about sentiment classification, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a methodology based on a predictive measure, which involves selecting an optimal source domain from a set of candidates. This methodology involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of distance functions between probability distributions, which could fall under the categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
